Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Community policing, protest and riots
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yljmv
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 12 Aug 1994
The FBI's powers, the need for "community policing", and the history of protest at UC Berkley are discussed by Alistair Cooke following a riot in Harlem Heights.